tldr: The user requested to implement database storage, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication for a sleep questionnaire application. The project successfully
  implemented a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, API routes for data management,
  and a simplified Next.js middleware-based authentication system for the admin
  dashboard, all of which were verified through testing.
overview: The user aimed to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage, developing an admin dashboard for
  data access, and securing it with an authentication system, all in line with a
  provided SOW. The implementation involved updating the questionnaire's
  demographic fields, defining a  model in Prisma for a
  PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), and creating API endpoints for submitting,
  retrieving, and exporting data as CSV. A key decision was to simplify the
  authentication system to use Next.js middleware with a basic cookie, providing
  efficient route protection for the admin dashboard. All implemented features,
  including database interaction, authentication, and CSV export, were
  successfully tested and verified, ensuring the application's core data
  management capabilities.
